## Implementation

Create `cmd/bd/tips.go` with:

### Core Infrastructure
```go
type Tip struct {
    ID          string
    Condition   func() bool      // Should this tip be eligible?
    Message     string
    Frequency   time.Duration    // Minimum gap between showings
    Priority    int              // Higher = shown first when eligible
    Probability float64          // 0.0 to 1.0 - chance of showing
}

func maybeShowTip(store storage.Storage) {
    if jsonOutput || quietMode {
        return // Respect output flags
    }

    tip := selectNextTip(store)
    if tip != nil {
        fmt.Fprintf(os.Stdout, "\nðŸ’¡ Tip: %s\n", tip.Message)
        recordTipShown(store, tip.ID)
    }
}

func selectNextTip(store storage.Storage) *Tip {
    now := time.Now()
    var eligibleTips []Tip

    // Filter to eligible tips (condition + frequency check)
    for _, tip := range tips {
        if !tip.Condition() {
            continue
        }

        lastShown := getLastShown(store, tip.ID)
        if !lastShown.IsZero() && now.Sub(lastShown) < tip.Frequency {
            continue
        }

        eligibleTips = append(eligibleTips, tip)
    }

    if len(eligibleTips) == 0 {
        return nil
    }

    // Sort by priority (highest first)
    sort.Slice(eligibleTips, func(i, j int) bool {
        return eligibleTips[i].Priority > eligibleTips[j].Priority
    })

    // Apply probability roll (in priority order)
    for _, tip := range eligibleTips {
        if rand.Float64() < tip.Probability {
            return &tip
        }
    }

    return nil  // No tips won probability roll
}
```

### Probability Examples

```go
// High priority, high probability = shows often
{Priority: 90, Probability: 0.8}  // 80% chance when eligible

// High priority, medium probability = important but not spammy
{Priority: 100, Probability: 0.6}  // 60% chance

// Low priority, low probability = rare suggestion
{Priority: 30, Probability: 0.3}  // 30% chance
```

### Metadata Storage
Use existing metadata table to track:
- `tip_{id}_last_shown` - Timestamp of last display (RFC3339 format)
- `tip_{id}_dismissed` - User permanently dismissed (future feature)

### Integration Points
Call `maybeShowTip()` at end of:
- `bd list` - After showing issues
- `bd ready` - After showing ready work
- `bd create` - After creating issue
- `bd show` - After showing issue details

## Design Decisions
- Tips shown on stdout (informational, not errors)
- Respects `--json` and `--quiet` flags
- Frequency enforces minimum gap between showings
- Priority determines evaluation order
- Probability reduces spam (not every eligible tip shows)
- Store state in metadata table (no new files)
- Deterministic seed for testing (optional BEADS_TIP_SEED env var)

